The paper deals with medical image analysis using deep learning techniques, specifically focusing on synthesizing 3D objects in medical images with manipulable properties. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial discriminators, which is a common technique in generative models and falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of synthetic data to improve the performance of supervised learning systems, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with medical imaging, which falls under the medical imaging (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with 3D object synthesis, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
